title: Landslides, United States by County, 1960-2007
name: Landslides, United States by County, 1960-2007
description:
SHELDUS is a county-level data set for the U.S. on 18 different natural hazard event types along with property and crop losses, injuries, and fatalities for the period January 1960 through December 2005. The database was compiled to examine spatial and temporal variability in historical hazard events and associated losses. U.S. county boundaries are adjusted to 2000 designations. The data were derived from several existing national data sources, of which National Climatic Data Center's monthly Storm Data publications are the major data source.

Counties were geocoded for latitude and longitude at batchgeocode.com and gpsvisualizer.com/geocode. When multiple instances of the same county occurred, latitudes were altered slightly to ensure they would be picked up in Maker. Therefore, latitudes for some counties are not 100 percent accurate. They are approximate. Data was then uploaded into Finder and checked for accuracy.
